  "author_association": "MEMBER",
  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "Currently `assert` is used to mean multiple different things in the spec. It can indicate an impossible situation that means a bug in the spec if it is reached or an invalid block is being processed. We should standardise on a clear set of rules.\r\n\r\nI propose `assert` should be use exclusively for impossible situations that indicate a bug. There should be an exception (possibly with subclasses), `Invalid(str)` to indicate that a block, transaction, etc... is invalid. There will probably be a third set of exceptions to deal with reverts in the evm.",
